With the support of lectures, discussions and practical tasks, students will learn about the regulations shaping the development of communities and look for the most optimal opportunities for community development under the conditions of the existing policy measures and administrative framework. In parallel with classroom work, students working in groups will generate an action plan for the development of a specific community, which fits into the existing socio-economic, political, legal and cultural context and analyse the accompanying social impacts. The course ends with the defence of the elaborated action plan.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the subject is to provide theoretical knowledge and practical skills for planning and evaluating activities aimed at the development of communities, considering the opportunities and limitations of the surrounding socio-economic, political, legal and cultural environment and associated social impacts.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course student - has a systematic overview of legislation, development documents and policy measures related to community development at different levels of government; - can plan activities based on the goal of community development and relate them to the opportunities and limitations resulting from existing legal regulations, development goals and policy measures; - understands the general logic of social impact assessment, knows impact analysis methods and can apply them in performing primary impact analyses.
